##This woman has a deadline!

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

Recently, an Australian woman in Beijing

Running in the neighborhood without a mask,

And refused to cooperate with the community's epidemic prevention efforts

Cause for concern,

Today,@PING AN BEIJING, Bulletin!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Source: Beijing Daily

Women who run outside without a mask are asked to leave the country within a time limit

The Beijing Municipal Public Security Bureau reported that at around 1500 hours on March 15, a district health and epidemic prevention worker in Chaoyang Public Security Bureau reported to the police that a woman had refused to cooperate with the community epidemic prevention work.

After receiving the report, the Hujialou Subdistrict police station immediately rushed to the scene to start work. Liang, a 47-year-old Australian working for Bayer Healthcare, entered Beijing from Beijing Capital International Airport on March 14. Her work residence permit is valid until September 5,2020.

On the afternoon of March 15, Liang, who was supposed to be observing at home in the rented area, ran in the community without a mask. The Community Health and epidemic prevention staff found out and dissuaded her, but the person was emotional and refused to cooperate. Police arrived at the scene, Liang conducted a critical education, asked to strictly observe the epidemic prevention and control regulations, Liang said to obey the management, did not go out. Liang's behavior in the online exposure, attracted public attention, the Bayer of his dismissal.

On March 18, the Beijing Municipal Public Security Bureau, in accordance with Article sixty-seven of the Law of the People's Republic of China on entry and exit administration, decided to cancel Liang's work permit and leave the country within a specified time limit.

The woman has been fired from her unit

On the evening of March 17,@bayer China issued a statement saying that the person involved was indeed a Bayer employee and that the dismissal of the employee would take effect immediately in accordance with company regulations.
